 1. Variable
👉 Variable ek naam hota hai jisme hum data store karte hain taaki baad me use kar sakein.
🔹 2. Data Types
👉 Data types batate hain ki variable me kis type ka data hai.
Integer → poore number
Float → decimal number
String → text / words
🔹 3. Input
👉 Input ka use user se data lene ke liye hota hai.
🔹 4. Output
👉 Output ka use result screen par dikhane ke liye hota hai.
🔹 5. Type Casting
👉 Ek data type ko doosre data type me convert karna type casting kehlata hai.
🔹 6. Operators
👉 Operators ka use operations (jaise addition, comparison) karne ke liye hota hai.
Arithmetic → +, -, *, /
Comparison → >, <, ==
Logical → and, or
🔹 7. If-Else
👉 If-else ka use condition check karne ke liye hota hai aur uske basis par decision liya jata hai.
🔹 8. Loop
👉 Loop ka use kisi kaam ko baar-baar repeat karne ke liye hota hai.
🔹 9. While Loop
👉 While loop tab tak chalta hai jab tak condition true hoti hai.
🔹 10. For Loop
👉 For loop ka use fixed number of times ya sequence ke through loop chalane ke liye hota hai.
🔹 11. Break
👉 Break loop ko turant rok deta hai.
🔹 12. Continue
👉 Continue current iteration skip karke next iteration start kar deta hai.
🔹 13. List
👉 List ek collection hota hai jisme multiple values ek saath store ki ja sakti hain.
🔹 14. Index
👉 Index kisi list ya string ke element ka position hota hai (0 se start hota hai).
15. Function
👉 Function ek block of code hota hai jo ek specific kaam karta hai aur baar-baar use kiya ja sakta hai.
🔹 16. Argument / Parameter
👉 Function ko jo values di jati hain unhe arguments ya parameters kehte hain.
🔹 17. Return
👉 Return function ka result wapas bhejne ke liye use hota hai.
🔹 18. Module
👉 Module ek file hoti hai jisme pre-written code hota hai jo hum use kar sakte hain.
🔹 19. Random Module
👉 Random module ka use random values generate karne ke liye hota hai.
🔹 20. String Methods
👉 String methods special functions hote hain jo string par operations karte hain (jaise check, convert, etc.)
🧠 Golden Line
👉 “Programming = Input + Logic + Output”
1. f-string
👉 f-string ka use string ke andar variables ko easily include karne ke liye hota hai.
👉 Isme {} ke andar variable likhte hain aur value automatically aa jaati hai.
👉 Ye normal string formatting se fast aur readable hota hai.
🔹 2. List (Detail)
👉 List ek ordered collection hota hai jisme multiple values store hoti hain.
👉 List mutable hoti hai (change ho sakti hai).
🔹 3. append()
👉 append() ka use list ke end me ek nayi value add karne ke liye hota hai.
🔹 4. insert()
👉 insert() ka use kisi specific position par value add karne ke liye hota hai.
🔹 5. remove()
👉 remove() ka use kisi specific value ko list se delete karne ke liye hota hai.
🔹 6. pop()
👉 pop() ka use last element ko remove karne ke liye hota hai
👉 Ya index dekar specific element bhi remove kar sakte hain.
🔹 7. sort()
👉 sort() list ke elements ko ascending (chhote se bade) order me arrange karta hai.
🔹 8. reverse()
👉 reverse() list ke order ko ulta kar deta hai.
🔹 9. len()
👉 len() ka use list ya string ki length (kitne elements hain) pata karne ke liye hota hai.
🔹 10. in keyword
👉 in ka use check karne ke liye hota hai ki koi value list me present hai ya nahi.
🔹 11. Tuple
👉 Tuple bhi list jaisa hota hai
👉 Par ye immutable hota hai (change nahi hota)
🔹 12. Dictionary (Basic idea)
👉 Dictionary key-value pair me data store karta hai.
👉 Example idea:
name → Jai
age → 17
👉 Fast access ke liye use hota hai
🔹 13. items()
👉 items() dictionary ke andar ke sabhi key-value pairs ko ek saath access karne ke liye use hota hai.
🔹 14. keys()
👉 keys() dictionary ki saari keys return karta hai.
🔹 15. values()
👉 values() dictionary ki saari values return karta hai.
🧠 Extra Important Concepts
🔹 Mutable vs Immutable
👉 Mutable:
change ho sakta hai (List)
👉 Immutable:
change nahi hota (String, Tuple)
🔹 Indexing
👉 Har element ka position hota hai
👉 Index 0 se start hota hai
🔹 Slicing (Basic idea)
👉 List ya string ka chhota part nikalna slicing kehlata hai.
🎯 Super Short Revision Trick
👉 Yaad rakh:
append → add
remove → delete
pop → last delete
sort → arrange
reverse → ulta
💪 Final Line
👉 “List + Loop + Condition = 80% Python power 🔥”
